7. Technical Architecture
7.1 Stack [DECISION]
Framework: Next.js (App Router) + React + TypeScript.
Styling: Tailwind CSS + a small design-token layer (config/brand.ts). Optionally shadcn/ui for admin components.
Animation: GSAP + ScrollTrigger, Framer Motion, Lottie (lottie-react), Three.js via @react-three/fiber + drei (lazy).
Database: PostgreSQL. ORM: Prisma. (Managed PG: Supabase or Neon.)
Auth: Auth.js (NextAuth) with credentials/email + optionally phone OTP via MSG91/Twilio (India phone-first). Admin role gated.
File/image storage: S3-compatible (AWS S3, Cloudflare R2, or Supabase Storage) + Cloudinary/next/image for delivery & transforms.
Payments: Razorpay (India). Stripe left as an interface-compatible future adapter.
Email/notifications: Resend or AWS SES (transactional); WhatsApp/SMS via MSG91 for order updates (India-relevant).
AI: Anthropic Claude API for slogan generation (§9). Verify current model IDs and pricing against Anthropic docs at build time — do not hardcode from memory.
Search: Postgres full-text for launch; upgrade to Meilisearch/Typesense if needed.
Hosting: Vercel (frontend + API routes) + managed Postgres (Neon/Supabase). Alt: a single VPS with Docker if cost-optimizing later.
Analytics: GA4 + a privacy-friendly option (Plausible/PostHog). PostHog also for funnels.
7.2 Rendering strategy
Homepage: mostly static/ISR shell + client animation layer.
Catalog & PDP: ISR (revalidate on product change via webhook/tag revalidation) for speed + SEO.
Cart/checkout/account/admin: client + server actions, no caching of personal data.
