9. AI Design Auto-Generation Engine (the "one-click" admin feature)
This is the owner's key feature: admin clicks a button, the system generates T-shirt designs (slogan + mockup) as drafts, then a human approves before publish. [DECISION: approval required.]
9.1 Pipeline (end to end)
[Admin clicks "Generate"] with params: {tier, collection, count, tone, garment/color}

        │

        ▼

1. SLOGAN GENERATION (Claude API)

   - System prompt encodes brand voice + tier definitions + moderation policy + few-shot from

     the slogan bank (§4).

   - Ask for N candidate slogans as strict JSON (use tool/JSON mode). Include for each:

     {slogan, tier, rationale, riskFlags[]}.

   - De-duplicate against existing DB slogans (normalized text + embedding similarity).

        │

        ▼

2. MODERATION GATE (automated, pre-human)

   - Run each slogan through a policy check (rules + a Claude moderation pass §16).

   - Reject anything hateful/targeting protected classes/defamatory/naming real companies or

     individuals. Flag borderline for human.

        │

        ▼

3. MOCKUP RENDERING (the "overlay text on blank tees")

   - Pick a BlankTemplate (one of the ~23 blanks) matching requested garment/color.

   - Composite the slogan text onto the template's printArea using its printAreaJson

     (position, size, perspective/warp) — server-side image generation:

       * Recommended: `sharp` + SVG text layer, or `node-canvas`, composited over the blank PNG.

       * Auto-fit: font size, line breaks, and layout chosen to fit the print area; support the

         monospace "Operator" style and the heavy display style.

       * Output: web preview (PNG/WebP) + a high-res print-ready file placeholder (for POD later).

        │

        ▼

4. DRAFT PRODUCT CREATION

   - Create Design + Product(status = PENDING_REVIEW, aiGenerated = true) + default Variants

     (colors/sizes from template) + generated preview images.

        │

        ▼

5. ADMIN REVIEW QUEUE (§10)

   - Admin sees a grid of generated drafts: slogan, tier, mockup, risk flags.

   - Actions per item: Approve & Publish | Edit | Regenerate mockup | Reject.

   - Bulk approve for clearly-safe Tier 1 items.
9.2 Slogan generation prompt (spec for the agent to implement)
System prompt must include: brand identity + voice (§2.6), the exact tier definitions and examples (§3.1), the full moderation policy (§16), and an instruction to produce original lines (no copying known trademarked slogans, no real company/person names).
Output contract: strict JSON array; validate with Zod; reject malformed responses and retry with a repair instruction.
Controls exposed to admin: tier, collection/theme, count (e.g., 10–30), tone slider (dry ↔ chaotic), and an optional keyword/seed ("appraisal", "WFH", "manager").
Trend input (optional Phase 2): allow pasting a trending phrase/topic; the model riffs on it originally. Do NOT auto-scrape or copy others' designs.
Verify the current Claude model ID and pricing from Anthropic docs at implementation time. Do not hardcode a model name from memory; put it in env/config.
9.3 Mockup engine details
BlankTemplate.printAreaJson defines the printable rectangle + optional 4-point warp so text sits realistically on the garment.
Provide 2–3 layout presets per tier (centered big, top-line/bottom-line, monospace terminal block for Operator collection).
Cache rendered previews in object storage; store URLs on the Design/Product.
Keep a clean separation: preview render (fast, web) vs print render (300 DPI, CMYK-safe, used only when POD is wired §12).
9.4 Cost & rate control
Batch slogan generation in one API call where possible; cap N per run.
Log token usage per generation run to AuditLog/a GenerationRun record for cost tracking.


