11. Payments, Checkout, Tax (India)
11.1 Gateway [DECISION: Razorpay]
Server creates a Razorpay Order (amount in paise) → client opens Razorpay Checkout (UPI, cards, netbanking, wallets) → on success, verify the signature server-side before marking paid → handle the Razorpay webhook as the source of truth (idempotent).
Never trust the client success callback alone; always verify signature + webhook.
Store razorpayOrderId/paymentId/signature, method, and status transitions.
11.2 UPI-first UX
India is UPI-dominant — ensure UPI is the top payment option, with cards/netbanking/wallets below. Consider UPI intent on mobile.
11.3 COD (Cash on Delivery)
Offer COD (huge in India) but gate it: min/max order value, pincode serviceability, optional partial prepaid for high-value/COD-abuse control. Flag COD orders separately in admin.
11.4 Checkout flow
Guest checkout allowed (capture email/phone) + optional account creation post-purchase.
Steps: cart → address (pincode autofill city/state) → shipping method → review → pay.
Apply coupon; show tax + shipping breakdown clearly.
Abandoned-cart capture (email/WhatsApp) — Phase 2.
11.5 Tax / GST [OWNER-INPUT — CA/accountant to confirm]
Apparel GST in India is slab-based by price point; the exact rate must be confirmed with a chartered accountant — do NOT hardcode a rate from memory. Make GST rate(s) configurable in admin settings, computed per line item, and shown on invoice.
Generate GST-compliant invoices (seller GSTIN, HSN code for garments, tax breakup). GSTIN, legal entity name, and address are [OWNER-INPUT].
11.6 Shipping
Integrate an aggregator (Shiprocket/Delhivery) for rates, label, pickup, tracking — Phase 1 can start manual (flat/free-over-threshold) and add aggregator API in Phase 2.
Serviceability check by pincode at checkout.


12. Print-on-Demand Integration (spec now, wire later)
