16.3 Content moderation policy (critical — this brand is edgy)
Because slogans are the product (and AI-generated), a strict, enforced policy is required. Allowed: mocking corporate systems, generic managers, meetings, WFH/WFO debates, burnout, appraisals, jargon — punching up at institutions and sideways at shared experience. Prohibited (auto-reject in the moderation gate §9.2):

Hate, slurs, or targeting any protected class (race, religion, caste, gender, sexuality, disability, nationality).
Naming/defaming real companies, brands, or identifiable individuals.
Sexual content, harassment, threats, self-harm, illegal activity.
Copying trademarked slogans or others' designs. Borderline items are flagged for human review, never auto-published. Tier 3 items always get human eyes. Keep an audit trail of moderation decisions.


17. Security & Performance
Payments: verify Razorpay signatures + webhooks server-side; idempotent order handling; never store card/UPI credentials.
Input: Zod-validate every API/route/form/webhook; parameterized queries via Prisma.
Auth: httpOnly secure cookies, CSRF protection on mutations, rate-limit auth + OTP + AI-generation endpoints, brute-force lockout.
Headers: strict CSP (allowlist for GSAP/Three/Razorpay/analytics), HSTS, X-Frame-Options, Referrer-Policy.
Secrets: env only + platform secret manager; never in repo; rotate keys.
Admin: role-gated, audit-logged, separate rate limits, optional 2FA.
Data: DPDP-aligned retention; PII encrypted at rest where feasible; least-privilege DB user.
Perf: ISR/edge caching for catalog; image optimization; code-split heavy libs; DB indexes; Core Web Vitals budgets (LCP<2.5s, CLS<0.1, INP<200ms).
Reliability: error monitoring (Sentry), uptime checks, DB backups + tested restore.


18. DevOps, Environments & Deployment
Environments: local → staging → production, each with its own DB + keys.
Hosting: Vercel (app) + Neon/Supabase (Postgres) + R2/S3 (assets). All secrets in the platform's env manager.
CI/CD: GitHub Actions — lint, typecheck, unit tests, Playwright e2e, Prisma migrate check, preview deploys per PR, protected main.
DB migrations: Prisma Migrate; never edit prod schema by hand; seed script for demo data + slogan bank + blank templates.
Testing: unit (domain/pricing/tax), integration (payments with Razorpay test mode, webhooks), e2e (browse→cart→checkout→order), moderation-gate tests (must block prohibited slogans). Use Razorpay test keys for all non-prod.
Observability: Sentry (errors), PostHog/GA4 (product), structured logs, alerting on failed payments/webhooks.


