22. Definition of Done / Acceptance Criteria
MVP is "done" when all are true:

A guest and a logged-in user can browse, filter by tier/collection, open a PDP, add to cart, and complete a real Razorpay payment (UPI + card + COD), with server-side signature + webhook verification.
Order is recorded with price snapshots, GST breakup, and a confirmation email is sent.
Admin can log in (role-gated), CRUD products/variants/collections/coupons, and manage/mark orders shipped with tracking.
Homepage scroll narrative works, respects prefers-reduced-motion, and hits performance budgets (LCP<2.5s on 4G); the site is fully shoppable with animations disabled.
All policy pages present (templated, marked for legal review); DPDP-aligned consent.
Mobile-first responsive; Lighthouse (mobile) perf/SEO/a11y ≥ 90.
Secrets only in env; Razorpay test mode in non-prod; CI green (lint, types, unit, e2e).

AI Studio (Phase 2) is "done" when:

Admin clicks "Generate", gets N slogans in the chosen tier, each auto-checked by the moderation gate; prohibited content is blocked automatically (covered by tests).
Slogans render onto blank-tee mockups within the defined print area; drafts appear in the review queue; admin can approve/edit/regenerate/reject; only approved items publish.
Every generation + moderation decision is audit-logged with token/cost tracking.

POD (Phase 3) is "done" when:

Flipping a product to POD mode auto-creates the POD product/order on payment, ingests tracking, and shows it in admin — with self-fulfillment still available per product.


